gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 127, Lakers 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Bradley Beals season-high 37 points (20 in the 3rd quarter), the Suns defeated the Lakers, 127-109. Beal added six rebounds, four assists and a season-high eight 3PM, while Devin Booker added 31 points, five rebounds, five assists and three steals for the Suns in the victory. LeBron James tallied 10 points, five rebounds and nine assists for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 20-18 on the season, while the Lakers fall to 19-20.
